4. Consider the function defined by

$$
\begin{gathered}
y=3 x \quad \text { for } \quad x \leq \frac{1}{2} \\
y=3(1-x) \quad \text { for } \quad x \geq \frac{1}{2}
\end{gathered}
$$

Show that this function maps the Cantor set into itself. [Hint: Use the ternary representation and see what happens under the above maps].
